<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-03-26T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-03-26T12:00:00-05:00" n="63" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d63">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01 Manchuria/1046: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-03-26T12:00:00-05:00">March 26,
                                1934—noon</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>38. Press reports from London have stated that the British Government has
                            instructed the British Ambassador that, in case Pu Yi makes an official
                            visit to Tokyo and invitations are issued for attendance at functions in
                            his honor, the Ambassador is not to attend.</p>
                        <p>In case any such situation develops, please report immediately the facts
                            and add your comments, thus enabling the Department to give you
                            appropriate instruction.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>